title: Tour of Washington County Stage Race
Highway To Heaven Hill Climb Time Trial
2011 MABRA Championships/ Church Creek Time Trial
St. Michaels Historic Century, Presented by Bike D
description:
Brief Description
Be a part of the Bike Doctor Tradition! We are offering three routes to accommodate everyone\'s needs - from the bicycle club member to the recreational enthusiast - 30, 62.5, and 100 miles. Our flat country roads are great for training as well as sightseeing. This year, we proudly support Team4Mil and the Wounded Warrior Project\'s Adaptive Cycling Program. Join members of the 2011 RAAM team and Wounded Warrior cyclists for this memorable event!
course:
Additional Information
All routes begin and end in St. Michaels. The rest stops are strategically placed to allow riders to relax and see expansive views to the water. The full Century route has a 20-minute ferry ride across the Tred Avon River to Oxford. There will be support staff at St. Michael\'s Elementary School and staffed aid stations along the route. Check in and late Registration for the ride begins at 7:00 a.m. Start time is at 8:00 a.m., and strongly urge everyone to leave at this time. Riders can pick up their registration packets at the St. Michaels Elementary School. T-Shirts will be given to Pre-Registered Riders ONLY. Day of registration is $50/rider.
